WEBVTT

00:05:00.014 --> 00:05:01.649
MK: I observed.

00:05:01.673 --> 00:05:07.903
I remember trying to follow the girls
who looked nice and happy and popular.

00:05:07.927 --> 00:05:11.252
You know, even in kindergarten,
you can tell who the popular kids are.

00:05:11.276 --> 00:05:14.244
AG: It sounds like you were a detective
as a kindergartener.

00:05:14.268 --> 00:05:15.466
MK: I think I had to be.

00:05:15.490 --> 00:05:17.664
I think that's a very good
way of putting it.

00:05:17.688 --> 00:05:18.990
I have thought in the past

00:05:19.014 --> 00:05:24.994
that my fascination with language
and with words comes from that early age.

00:05:25.018 --> 00:05:28.851
AG: That fascination quickly turned
into a vivid career aspiration.

00:05:28.875 --> 00:05:32.779
MK: Apparently, I announced at dinner,
when I was five or six years old,